replies.bodyText:
I ran in to an interesting issue when I was playing around with this. I changed the definition of LeapDeviceDiscoveryService to the following:
public class LeapDeviceDiscoveryService extends AbstractDiscoveryService implements DiscoveryService, ThingHandlerService

But then I got an error indicating a conflict between AbstractDiscoveryService and the ThingHandlerService interface:
The inherited method AbstractDiscoveryService.deactivate() cannot hide the public abstract method in ThingHandlerService

They do seems to define deactivate() in incompatible ways:
AbstractDiscoveryService:
    protected void deactivate() {
        if (backgroundDiscoveryEnabled) {
            stopBackgroundDiscovery();
        }
    }

ThingHandlerService:
    default void deactivate() {
    }

Anyway, I'm starting to think that changing this to a ThingHandlerService  may not be worth the effort.

